title: Isaiah Thomas on possible Boston Celtics return: 'Anything can happen'
summary: In a surprising turn of events, Isaiah Thomas tweeted Sunday night that with regard to a Boston Celtics return, “Anything can happen.” Anything is possible. Those were the iconic words screamed from the mountaintop of an NBA title by Kevin Garnett on the Garden floor in 2008 after he helped lead the Boston Celtics to their 17th title. It turns out that's exactly what was running through Isaiah Thomas' mind when he was asked if he would consider coming back to Boston this offseason. It's a surprising response from Thomas, who was bitter after his departure. author: rocky.j.mountain
title: Popovich, Spurs find 'silver lining' amid playoff struggle
summary: Quiet concern brews in the business and ticket offices of the San Antonio Spurs over the prospect of losing the revenue they'd come to expect like clockwork from advancing to 20 consecutive postseasons. Twenty-four starting lineups, 185 total games missed -- including 61 by star forward Kawhi Leonard -- yet not one player, coach or member of personnel has lost focus in the face of current circumstances. "It's been a frustrating season," Spurs coach Gregg Popovich said. Mounting losses and uncertainty about who will be on the court next to you on a given night -- not to mention not knowing when Leonard will return from a mysterious quad ailment -- could understandably fracture or at least stress relationships in a locker room; especially in an organization with such a long track record of success.

title: Top-seeded Kansas to face No. 5 seed Clemson Friday night in Omaha
summary: It's Kansas vs. Clemson on Friday night in Omaha, Neb., with a trip to the Elite Eight on the line. The top-seeded Jayhawks (29-7) will be playing for a third consecutive trip to the Elite Eight and the eighth in head coach Bill Self's 15 seasons at Kansas. The fifth-seeded Tigers (25-9), who thrashed No. 4 seed Auburn 84-53 on Sunday night in San Diego, will be playing for a spot in just their second Elite Eight in school history. Their only other trip came in 1980 and the Tigers are playing in just their 12th NCAA Tournament ever and first since 2011.
